	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">&lt;lavish praise upon authors&gt;<br />
Can I say first that this is yet another excellent feature of this site.  Thanks to all involved in the hard work.  You are doing an outstanding job.<br />
&lt;/lavish praise upon authors&gt;<br />
<br />
I agree with Maelarr.  *Iff* you wanted to do some more work...<br />
<br />
Perhaps reduce the rewards by factor of 5 then have a 1-5 rating system of threads.  The rating acts as a multiplier.  Can't rate your own thread.<br />
<br />
So I post a thread 10/5 = 2pp<br />
I get 13 replies 25/5 = 5pp<br />
I get 53 views 25/5 = 5pp<br />
Sub-total = 12pp<br />
Rating = 3<br />
Total = 36pp<br />
<br />
Just delay the posting of pp a week to let thread max out.  Any view/post after a week is ignored or gets a flat 1pp reward.<br />
<br />
Also, displaying the rating in the thread summary page would give an idea of how helpful others found the thread to be before we read it.<br />
<br />
Then again, having a rating system can provide too negative a response to some posters and that might drive some people away from the site.  Maybe the egalitarian approach is better?  What does everyone else think?<br />
<br />
Also, what's to stop the folks starting their own thread instead of replying.  I could have called this "Suggestions for the new money system" and stolen a whole lot of replies.   But hey, we're all grown ups so maybe this isn't an issue.  <img src="images/smilies/orangesmilewinkgrin.gif" border="0" alt=""></font></p>
	
	<p></p>
	<p></p>
	</td></tr></table>
