	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">Well, I don't want to rewrite the system just for the rating system. Speaking from years of experience with websites and message boards; not many people will end up using the rating system. Heck, i couldn't even get people to rate threads before we got the store installed, and I even moved the rate thread right above the text field in the reply window and made it a different color etc, so I'm not too worried about it at this point.<br />
<br />
Let's test this system for a month or so, then we can make adjustments based on usage etc. This is just a fun feature installed to give you members some incentive for posts you're already making.<br />
<br />
Oh, and keep in mind. Starting to spoof threads on existing topics will be grounds for a warning and removal of thread, merging it with the original thread and giving the original thread starter credit for your hard work trying to earn extra pp. Also, on repeated abuse of the store system you will be banned from the store. You can continue to post and participate on the message board and website but will not be able to accumulate pp or spend your pp in the store. That should be enough to discourage people from trying to gain extra pp. <br />
<br />
Trust me, those of you who have contributed greatly to this website up until now will receive plenty of pp. Just look at some of the past threads receiving 50-60 replies and 1-2000 views. Those will come again, and the creator will make a lot of pp.<br />
<br />
Like I said...this is suppose to be fun, so dont' take it too seriously. We're not trying to build a strong economy here or set up trading posts etc. It's just a system created to reward the most active users in ways, as well as motivating the less active people to participate in the system.<br />
<br />
I appreciate any feedback of course, so keep playing with the system and tell me what you think.<br />
<br />
As for the rabid dark elf's question about the pp accumulation being broke: It works on all your threads, so even though you just clicked on one post and saw your pp jump up quite a bit, that can come from people replying to/viewing other threads of yours etc. If people are working with 4-5 threads/posts of yours, then surely it is going to jump a bit.<br />
<br />
Dark Elf Tax still being worked on. All dark elves on the site will have 2pp withdrawn from their account on a daily basis... <img src="images/smilies/orangewink.gif" border="0" alt=""></font></p>
	
